#   CODE-012: woof/CONN.c: abc unescape/escape, slice slots

woof/CONN.c hand-rolls percent-decoding (= URIu8sUnesc), copies dog/HUNK.c's html-escape verbatim, and manages per-conn buffers with raw pointer arithmetic over WOOF.pool. It also duplicates the HTTP-200+HTML-prelude emit and the free-slot reset. Route through abc/URI and a shared html-escape, and carve slots with abc slices.

##  Issues

Percent-decode, html-escape, and slot buffers are hand-rolled; prelude/reset pasted.

 -  WOOFutf8ExtractURI (CONN.c:368) hand-rolls %XX decode via BASE16rev = abc URIu8sUnesc.
 -  html_escape_into (CONN.c:351) is a copy of dog/HUNK.c:642 hunk_html_escape.
 -  per-conn buffers via ptr-arith over WOOF.pool (CONN.c:123,182,868) — CLAUDE.md §10.
 -  HTTP-200+prelude emit pasted CONN.c:687/806; free-slot reset pasted CONN.c:142,185, WOOF.c:151.

##  Blockers

None, but html-escape is cross-dir with dog — expose one shared helper, do not re-copy.

##  Planned

abc URIu8sUnesc + a shared html-escape; slice-carved slots; one prelude + one reset.

 -  Repro first (§17): woof serves a URI with %XX and HTML-special chars; output unchanged.
 -  Percent-decode → URIu8sUnesc; html-escape → a shared dog helper.
 -  Carve WOOF.pool slots with abc slices; one prelude emit; one slot-reset.

